<ol start="9" class="ol_one_padding">
  <li><strong>SUPPRESSION OF FACTS OR MIS-STATEMENT </strong></li>
</ol>
<p>If any declaration/information given by you to the Company proves to be false or if you are found to have willfully suppressed any material information, you will be liable to removal from employment by the Company at any time without any notice.</p>
<ol start="10">
  <li><strong>MISCONDUCT</strong></li>
</ol>
<p>In the event of your committing any misconduct or acting contrary to Company's rules or company&rsquo;s business interests, you will be liable for disciplinary action (including termination of service with/without notice) as per Company rules applicable to you.</p>
<ul>
  <li>Breach of Company&rsquo;s standards with respect to integrity, ethics, honesty, sincerity and loss of confidence</li>
  <li>Failure to follow the rules and regulations of the Company</li>
  <li>Any instance of giving false information, misrepresentation of facts, or any willful suppression of material information</li>
  <li>Guilty of moral turpitude or of dishonesty in dealing with company&rsquo;s materials or documents, or theft or misappropriation of company&rsquo;s property regardless of the value involved</li>
  <li>Gross negligence or carelessness or inefficiency in performing duties</li>
  <li>Unauthorized absence</li>
  <li>Sexual harassment</li>
  <li>Use of vile, intemperate, or abusive language; fighting, pushing, or acting in a threatening manner to another employee, customer/vendor or visitor</li>
  <li>Submission of false personal records, reports, time sheets, travel statement bills, records, logs, etc.</li>
  <li>Unauthorized possession and/or improper accounting, replication and/or sale of company software or other material</li>
  <li>Willful destruction of the organization&rsquo;s property or any acts of sabotage</li>
  <li>Failure or refusal to carry out any lawful and reasonable instruction from the Supervisors or deviation from Standard Operating Procedures.</li>
  <li>Inciting others to commit breach of law and/or company&rsquo;s rules and&nbsp;regulations.</li>
  <li>Working against the interest of the company or leakage of any information which may be used against the company&rsquo;s interests.</li>
  <li>Conviction by a court of law for a crime.</li>
</ul>
<ol start="11">
  <li><strong>SEPARATION</strong></li>
</ol>
<p>Before your separation from the company on account of any reason whatsoever you will immediately return to the Company (before you are relieved) all correspondence, specifications, formulae, passwords, books, documents, cost data, market data, literature, drawings, effects or records etc, or any company property given to you by the Company. You shall not make or retain copies of any documents/files.</p>
